it.riccardotraverso.java.lang

Class MultiIterator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.riccardotraverso.java.lang.MultiIterator<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the elements iterated through by each of the collected iterators. It is not mandatory that individual iterators are exactly of type Iterator<E>, they might be of any other type Iterator<E1> as long as E1 extends or implements E.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<E>

    public class MultiIterator<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<E>
    A MultiIterator collects a sequence of simple iterators in order to provide a convenient way to navigate through each of them. MultiIterator returns each element of each iterator, transparently moving to the next iterator as soon as the one currently used does not have any more elements.
